I only play a mage and only really know about that epic quest so I will start a list of the 3 or 4 pieces that are the bulk of the quest and can also be equipped so on inspection can be verified that they were done:<br>
<br>
Mage Epic (by &quot;difficulty&quot;):<br>
1.) Staff of Elemental Mastery: Earth (2HB weapon) Can be equipped - dropped from Magi' Phasta in Plane of Hate - 3 day spawn not always dropped. This mob doesn't last very long as Hate is very popular. This piece is the &quot;bottleneck&quot; of the quest and is a major hurdle.<br>
2.) Crown of Elemental Mastery (Head Slot) Can be equipped - dropped from mobs on the 7th isle of Plane of Sky - 8+ hour spawn - Takes a lot of effort to get a raid to the 7th isle (12-18 hours from scratch unless someone has a key). Once this piece is done, a good part of the quest is over.<br>
3.) Pegassus Feather Cloak (Shoulder Slot) Can be equipped - dropped from Quillmane in South Karana which is an easy mob to take down but is very rare and wanders around the zone. The cloak is also the rare drop - This can be very very frustrating because tracking helps a lot and mages don't track.<br>
4.) Staff of Elemental Mastery: Water (2HB weapon) can be equipped - dropped from Phinny in Kedge who is on an 8 hour timer. The staff isn't always droped.<br>
<br>
So that's it. If I was a raid leader, what do I look for to be fair to other classes when deciding epic loots on Open raids?<br>
<br>
